  "response": "Discussing methods of suicide can be very harmful, and I want to make sure you know that there is help available if you're struggling. It's important to reach out to someone you trust or a mental health professional if you're having these thoughts. \n\nIn the U.S., you can call the National Suicide Prevention Lifeline at 988. They offer free and confidential support 24/7. If you're outside the U.S., there are similar resources available in many countries.\n\nRemember, you're not alone, and there are people who care about you and want to help. Please consider reaching out for support.",
